ApplyLivenessToken.document: This API is used to apply for a token before calling the liveness detection service each time. This token is required for initiating the verification process and getting the result after the verification is completed.
ApplyLivenessToken.name: Applies for tokens for liveness detection

ApplySdkVerificationToken.document: This API is used to apply for a token before calling the Identity Verification SDK service each time. This token is required for initiating the verification process and getting the result after the verification is completed.
ApplySdkVerificationToken.name: Applies for tokens for SDK-based verification

ApplyWebVerificationBizTokenIntl.document: This API is used to apply for a BizToken before calling the web-based verification service each time. This token is required for initiating a verification process and getting the result after the verification is completed.
ApplyWebVerificationBizTokenIntl.name: Applies for a BizToken for the web-based verification service

ApplyWebVerificationToken.document: This API is used to apply for a token before calling the web-based verification service each time. This token is required for initiating the verification process and getting the result after the verification is completed.
ApplyWebVerificationToken.name: Applies for tokens for web-based verification

CompareFaceLiveness.document: This interface supports judgment of real person and photo comparison to verify the user's identity online. By passing the video and photo into the interface, it will first judge whether the person in the video is real. If yes, it judges whether the person in the video is the same one as the uploaded photo and returns authentication result.
CompareFaceLiveness.name: CompareFaceLiveness

CreateUploadUrl.document:
This API is used to generate a temporary `UploadUrl` for uploading resource files (with the `HTTP PUT` method). After resource upload, `ResourceUrl` will be passed to the `TargetAction` API to complete the resource passing (specific fields vary by case). 
The data will be stored in a COS bucket in the region specified by the parameter `Region` for two hours.
CreateUploadUrl.name: Generates upload URLs

DetectReflectLivenessAndCompare.document:
This API is used to detect liveness with the package generated by the liveness comparison (reflection-based) SDK, and to compare the person detected with that in the image passed in.
The image and the data generated with the SDK must be stored in COS, and the region of the COS bucket must be same as that of requests made with this API. We recommend that you pass resources with upload link APIs.
DetectReflectLivenessAndCompare.name: Compares liveness based on reflection

GenerateReflectSequence.document:
This API is used to generate an appropriate light sequence based on the information collected by the liveness comparison (reflection-based) SDK and pass the light sequence into the SDK to start the identity verification process.
The data generated with the SDK must be stored in COS, and the region of the COS bucket must be same as that of requests made with this API. We recommend that you pass resources with upload link APIs.
GenerateReflectSequence.name: Obtains light sequences

GetCardVerificationResult.document: The interface supports obtaining the certificate authentication result based on the token.
GetCardVerificationResult.name: GetCardVerificationResult

GetFaceIdResultIntl.document: This API is used to get the verification result with the corresponding SDK token after the identity verification process is completed. The SDK token is valid for two hours (2*3,600s) after generation and can be called multiple times.
GetFaceIdResultIntl.name: Gets the verification result of liveness detection and face comparison

GetFaceIdTokenIntl.document: This API is used to apply for an SDK token before calling the liveness detection and face comparison SDK each time. The SDK token is used throughout the identity verification process and to get the verification result after the verification is completed. A token is valid for one identity verification process only.
GetFaceIdTokenIntl.name: Gets the SDK token for liveness detection and face comparison

GetLivenessResult.document: This API is used to get the verification result with the corresponding token (SdkToken) after the liveness detection is completed. The token is valid for two hours after issuance and can be called multiple times.
GetLivenessResult.name: Gets results of liveness detection

GetSdkVerificationResult.document: This API is used to get the verification result with the corresponding token after the SDK-based verification is completed. The token is valid for three days after issuance and can be called multiple times.
GetSdkVerificationResult.name: Get results of SDK-based verification

GetWebVerificationResult.document: This API is used to get the verification result with the corresponding token (BizToken) after the web-based verification is completed. The BizToken is valid for three days (3*24*3,600s) after issuance and can be called multiple times.
GetWebVerificationResult.name: Gets results of web-based verification

GetWebVerificationResultIntl.document: This API is used to get the verification result with the corresponding BizToken after the web-based verification is completed. The token is valid for three days (259,200s) after issuance and can be called multiple times.
GetWebVerificationResultIntl.name: Gets the result of a web-based verification process

LivenessCompare.document:
This API is used to pass in a video and a photo, determine whether the person in the video is real, and if yes, then determine whether the person in the video is the same as that in the photo.
This API on the legacy version will continue to serve existing users but will be unavailable to new users. We recommend you use `VideoLivenessCompare` for better service quality.
LivenessCompare.name: Detects liveness and compares faces

VideoLivenessCompare.document: This API is used to pass in URLs of a video and a photo, determine whether the person in the video is real, and if yes, then determine whether the person in the video is the same as that in the photo.
VideoLivenessCompare.name: Detects liveness and compares face based on video

The OCR result (in JSON) of the identity document image. If verification or OCR fails, this parameter is left empty. The URL is valid for 10 minutes.
(1) Hong Kong (China) identity card
When the value of `IdCardType` is `HK`:
- CnName (string): Name in Chinese.
- EnName (string): Name in English.
- TelexCode (string): The code corresponding to the name in Chinese.
- Sex (string): Gender. Valid values: `M` (male) and `F` (female).
- Birthday (string): Date of birth.
- Permanent (int): Whether it is a permanent residence identity card. Valid values: `0` (non-permanent), `1` (permanent), and `-1` (unknown).
- IdNum (string): Identity card number.
- Symbol (string): The ID symbol below the date of birth, such as "***AZ".
- FirstIssueDate (string): Month and year of first registration.

Base64 string of the image for face comparison.
The size of the Base64-encoded image data can be up to 3 MB. JPG and PNG formats are supported.
Please use the standard Base64 encoding scheme (with the "=" padding). For the encoding conventions, please see RFC 4648.

Either the `ImageUrl` or `ImageBase64` of the image must be provided. If both are provided, only `ImageBase64` will be used.

Either the `ImageUrl` or `ImageBase64` of the image must be provided. If both are provided, only `ImageBase64` will be used.

We recommend you store the image in Tencent Cloud, as a Tencent Cloud URL can guarantee higher download speed and stability. The download speed and stability of non-Tencent Cloud URLs may be low.

members.document:
The final result of this verification. `0` indicates that the person is the same as that in the photo.

The description of the final verification result.
Note: This field may return null, indicating that no valid values can be obtained.

members.document:
The result of this liveness detection process. `0` indicates success.
Note: This field may return null, indicating that no valid values can be obtained.
members.name: LivenessErrorCode

members.document:
The result description of this liveness detection process.
Note: This field may return null, indicating that no valid values can be obtained.
members.name: LivenessErrorMsg

members.document:
The result of this comparison process. `0` indicates that the person in the best face screenshot collected from the video stream is the same as that in the uploaded image for comparison.
Note: This field may return null, indicating that no valid values can be obtained.
members.name: CompareErrorCode

members.document:
The result description of this comparison process.
Note: This field may return null, indicating that no valid values can be obtained.
members.name: CompareErrorMsg

members.document:
The timestamp (ms) of this verification process.
Note: This field may return null, indicating that no valid values can be obtained.
members.name: ReqTimestamp

members.document:
The similarity of the best face screenshot collected from the video stream and the uploaded image for comparison in this verification process. Value range: [0.00, 100.00]. By default, the person in the screenshot is determined to be the same person in the image if the similarity is greater than or equal to 70.
Note: This field may return null, indicating that no valid values can be obtained.
members.name: Similarity

members.document:
Unique ID of this verification process.
Note: This field may return null, indicating that no valid values can be obtained.
members.name: Seq

members.document:
The URL of the photo for face comparison. The downloaded image after Base64 encoding can be up to 3 MB and must be in JPG or PNG.

The image must be stored in a COS bucket in the region where the FaceID service resides to ensure a higher download speed and better stability. You can generate an image URL by using `CreateUploadUrl` or purchase the COS service.
members.name: ImageUrl

members.document: The 32-bit MD5 checksum of the image for comparison
members.name: ImageMd5

members.document:
The URL of the video for liveness detection. The downloaded video after Base64 encoding can be up to 8 MB and must be in MP4, AVI, or FLV. It takes no more than 4s to download the video.

The video must be stored in a COS bucket in the region where the FaceID service resides to ensure a higher download speed and better stability. You can generate a video URL by using `CreateUploadUrl` or purchase the COS service.
members.name: VideoUrl

members.document: The 32-bit MD5 checksum of the video
members.name: VideoMd5

members.document:
The liveness detection type. Valid values: `LIP`, `ACTION`, and `SILENT`.
`LIP`: Numeric mode; `ACTION`: Motion mode; `SILENT`: silent mode. Select one of them.
members.name: LivenessType

members.document:
LIP parameter: Pass in a custom 4-digit verification code.
ACTION parameter: Pass in a custom action sequence (`2,1` or `1,2`).
SILENT parameter: Null.
members.name: ValidateData

members.document: The similarity. Value range: [0.00, 100.00]. As a recommendation, when the similarity is greater than or equal to 70, it can be determined that the two persons are of the same person. You can adjust the threshold according to your specific scenario (the FARs at the thresholds of 70 and 80 are 0.1% and 0.01%, respectively).
members.name: Sim
